Kano state government has placed a ban on commercial tricycles popularly known as A Daidata Sahu from 10:00 pm-6:00 am. The movement restriction within the city takes effect from Thursday, July 21, 2022. Commissioner for Information, Muhammad Garba in a statement indicated that a decision to that effect was reached at the end of the state security meeting. He said the measure was part of efforts to ensure the security of lives and property in the state. The commissioner urged tricycle riders to comply with the stipulated hours or be prepared to face security enforcement. 